                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First off, I am only posting this question in this forum because it doesn't really fit anywhere else.  It's *NOT* that I'm assuming all women cook.  A good friend of mine cooks a lot and makes some great food (he just got married this past weekend too, and is out of town or I'd ask him my question).
<br />

<br />
Anyway, with that disclaimer out of the way, do any of you have a good recipe for a vodka sauce for pasta?  I've found a few on the 'net, but I don't know if one is better than another.  I'm just looking for some personal experiences.  Or heck, does anyone have a link to a good message board or web site for bachelors wanting to learn to cook for their new girlfriends?   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_shifty.gif" alt="eusa_shifty.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
Thanks,
<br />
-- C.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
