                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here's a real simple Vodka Sauce <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
1 quart Store-bought marinara sauce (smooth kind,, no chunks of any kind...or you can blend it up in a blender, processor, etc) 
<br />
1 cup vodka 
<br />
1/2 cup heavy cream, at room temperature 
<br />
1/2 cup grated Parmesan 
<br />

<br />
Simmer the tomato sauce and vodka in a heavy large skillet over <span style="font-weight: bold">low </span>heat until the mixture reduces by 1/4, <span style="font-weight: bold">stirring often</span>, about 20 minutes. Stir the cream into the tomato and vodka sauce. Simmer over low heat until the sauce is heated through. Stir in the Parmesan cheese until melted and well blended. ]
<br />

<br />
Also, if you prefer you can adjust the cheese to taste, or use other cheese (like Romano, Asiago, etc)
<br />

<br />
Serve over pasta</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
