                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I use cooking.com it has a great database for recipies. also, for a good cookbook, check out library used book sales, garage sales, and estate sales for a 30 or more year old Better homes and gardens cook book. you know the ones with the red and white checkerboard cover.  I have one thats about 40 years old and I swear its the best recipies ever made.
<br />
for the wine sauce. a simple but good one is Taking Burgandy, Chicken/beef broth, (1 cup broth 1 cup burgandy) and boiling it down in a saucepan, when cooked down about 1/3 of the way, add a corn starch mixture to it. (2 teaspoons corn starch to 3 tablespoons water) make sure the mixture is completely disolved and not lumpy, then add to broth/burgandy in pan stiring with a wisk constantly for 2 min. your done.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Serianna 56 Enchanter Innoruuk Server.
<br />
    \"Someone once told me your suicidal you know that? I dont know how you survived this long!\"  <img src="images/smiles/icon_hang.gif" alt="icon_hang.gif" border="0" />
